fuzz_extract_mem: assert `dmc_unrar_filters_get_first_length(&ctx->filters) > 0`
at dmc_unrar.c:7997 inside dmc_unrar_rar50_decompress. The RAR5 LZ
path pulls the next filter from the filter queue and expects its
length to be non-zero, but a malformed archive can declare a
zero-length filter via the unchecked VLQ at
dmc_unrar_filters_rar5_parse (dmc_unrar.c:12002). 195-byte input,
surfaced on the 60-second fuzz_extract_mem smoke run taken right
after Phase 6 caps (file-count/file-size/total-size/ratio/PPMd)
landed. Fixed by rejecting filter_length == 0 at parse time in both
the RAR4 and RAR5 filter parsers (shares the existing
DMC_UNRAR_FILTERS_INVALID_LENGTH return with the oversize check).
